Durban - A newborn baby girl was found abandoned on Thursday afternoon in some bushes next to Royston Road, Mountain Rise in Pietermaritzburg. ER24 paramedics were called to the scene by the SAPS Search and Rescue, requesting medical assistance. "Upon arrival, paramedics were handed a newborn baby girl by the SAPS. It is understood that the newborn had been found lying amongst the bushes near the road," said ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring. "Paramedics assessed the infant and found that she had sustained no injuries but was suffering from low body temperature. "The infant was immediately warmed and transported to a nearby hospital for further treatment," added Meiring. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. POST